==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fin de sicle
<hw>Fin` de si⟦egrave⟧"cle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[F.]</ety>
<def>Lit., end of the century; -- mostly used adjectively in English to
signify: belonging to, or characteristic of, the close of the 19th
century. At that time the phrase was also intended to imply
⟦ldquo⟧modern⟦rdquo⟧ or ⟦ldquo⟧up-to-date;⟦rdquo⟧ <as>as,
<ex>fin-de-si⟦egrave⟧cle</ex> ideas</as>.</def> <note>As the twentieth
century comes to a close, the meaning may change.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

